        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 2:16PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 216 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Oak Mountain State Park, or near Pelham. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hoover, Alabaster, Pelham, Helena, Chelsea, Indian Springs Village,
Inverness, Highland Lakes, Riverchase, Oak Mountain State Park, Oak
Mountain Amphitheater, Meadowbrook, Joe Tucker Park, Ballantrae,
Hoover Veterans Park, and Bounds Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
